  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dc3 \u0d9a\u0db4\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0d9f\u0da7 \u0daf\u0db8\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The head was cut off and thrown into the river",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Akuressa Police have launched an investigation into the search for a man who had cut his head off his neck and dumped it in the Nilwala River in the Thibbatuwa area in Akuressa, Matara this morning (27).",
        "The deceased has been identified as Vellalathanthrige Sumanapala (70), a disabled father of two, a resident of Ralakadawatta, Thibbatuwa, Akuressa.",
        "The homes of the deceased and the man suspected of beheading are adjacent and an argument broke out between the two parties this morning (27th) claiming that the deceased had flagged his house.",
        "It then escalated into a confrontation and the suspect went home and took a sword and tried to attack the disabled man. Although the wife and child of the disabled person had tried to prevent it, the suspect had cut off the head of the disabled person and run away. It is reported that the head was later thrown into the Nilwala river. Police have launched an investigation to find the head.",
        "The wife and child of the disabled person who managed to escape the dispute have been admitted to the Akuressa Hospital with minor injuries. The suspect Samarasinghe Thilanna has fled the area and a special police team has been deployed to arrest him and the Akuressa Police are conducting further investigations."
      ],
